-- EasyJet to Start Six New Routes From Edinburgh, Add Aircraft
-- B y   P e t e r   W o o d i f i e l d   a n d   K a r i   L u n d g r e n
-- 2012-10-11T14:32:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-11/easyjet-to-start-six-new-routes-from-edinburgh-add-aircraft-1-.html
EasyJet Plc (EZJ) , Europe’s second-largest
discount airline, said it will add routes from U.K. cities
Edinburgh and Manchester to destinations including Reykjavik,
Iceland.  Easyjet will base an additional two planes in the Scottish
capital, it said in a statement today. Other destinations out of
Edinburgh include Copenhagen, Prague, Croatia’s Dubrovnik, and
Hamburg and Berlin in Germany, EasyJet said. The flights will
bring an additional 140,000 passengers a year to Edinburgh.  The carrier will add one aircraft and five new routes out
of Manchester starting in February to destinations including
 Venice , Italy, Antalya in Turkey and the Greek islands of
Mykonos and Santorini.  To contact the reporters on this story:
